   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Eighty-eight AFTER DEATH THE JUDGMENT Scripture: Heb 9:27 It is reserved for men once to die Men deserve death.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Death came from sin.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>No one can escape death.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Give some examples to describe how man cannot escape death.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>After death comes judgment Death is not the end but a beginning.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Man s life is short, and this short life is ended by death.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>But after death there is eternity.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This eternity is ushered in by death.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Whatever man does in this age will be judged in eternity.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Many commit crimes and escape the punishment of the law and the shame of public opinion.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Many think they will be safe from punishment once they die.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>But what man does cannot be resolved by his death.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Actually death is not the end of all things.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Everything will be judged in the coming eternity.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The results of judgment There is not one who has never committed a sin in this age, so in eternity no one can escape God s righteous judgment and condemnation.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The result of condemnation is perdition.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Perdition means to go to hell.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The way to escape</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Give a strong conclusion on how to escape death and judgment.</S>
   </TEXT>
